        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): add listGroupsLive for real-time group directory",
        "body": "## Root Cause\n\nThe WhatsApp channel directory adapter only registered `listGroups` (which reads from the config map `channels.whatsapp.groups`) but did **not** register `listGroupsLive`. The CLI (and other consumers) prefer `listGroupsLive` when available, so users who have active WhatsApp group memberships but an empty config-based groups map would see an empty directory. No `listGroupsLive` implementation existed for WhatsApp.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Bug: WhatsApp directory `/groups` returned empty even when the account is a member of groups, because only the config-backed `listGroups` was wired up but not the live-fetch variant.\n- This PR adds `listWhatsAppDirectoryGroupsLive` that fetches groups from the Baileys socket via `groupFetchAllParticipating()`, with graceful fallback to config when the socket is unavailable or throws. The new function is registered in the channel directory adapter.\n- Fixes #76722\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/directory-config.test.ts` — 7/7 passed (5 new tests + 2 existing)\n- `pnpm check:changed` — pending; extension-only changes, no core surface affected\n- Autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- CI: pending\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp directory `/groups` now returns the account's real group memberships fetched live from the WhatsApp connection, not just config-declared groups.\nReal environment tested: Linux, Node 22, branch `fix/issue-76722-whatsapp-directory-groups-live` commit `496d97cca209f03fcc24b872761d4cf12e792dc1`\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\npnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/directory-config.test.ts\n```\nEvidence after fix:\n```console\n RUN  v4.1.7 /home/0668000452/codes/OPENSOURCES/openclaw\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  7 passed (7)\n  Start at  15:21:15\n  Duration  7.27s (transform 3.60s, setup 390ms, import 6.53s, tests 39ms, environment 0ms)\n```\nObserved result after fix: All 7 tests pass, including 5 new tests covering socket-unavailable fallback, live group fetching from Baileys socket, query filtering, limit application, socket error fallback, and empty groups.\nWhat was not tested: Live E2E with a real WhatsApp account (requires Crabbox with WhatsApp auth); the changes are extension-internal and follow established patterns from the Telegram channel's `listGroupsLive` implementation.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-76722-whatsapp-directory-groups-live",
